<b>Daily Star:Two more truckloads of weapons seized in Bekaa</b>

MASHARIH Al-QAA, Lebanon: The Lebanese Army confiscated overnight two truckloads of weapons from the border area of Masharih al-Qaa, a security source said Thursday.The source, speaking to The Daily Star on condition of anonymity, said the seized weapons were concealed in two Cold storage trucks parked on a side road in Masharih al-Qaa.No arrests were made during the Lebanese Army Raid in the area, the second in as many days.The military had arrested 10 armed Lebanese and Syrian men in the border village of Joura in Masharih al-Qaa Tuesday evening.The men were referred Thursday to the Beirut headquarters of the Lebanese Army intelligence, according to the source.At least five families from Joura, whose homes were hit by Syrian fire in recent days, were seen Thursday packing up their personal belongings and getting ready to flee to safer areas.
